research shows that father 's gene may affect children 's date of birth
( agence france - presse , paris , 28 th ) - according to a research report by a british medical weekly published on saturday , the gene of the father may affect the date of the child 's birth .
about 5 percent of pregnant women will be able to produce later , that is , the time of pregnancy will reach 294 days .
at present , it has been known that this issue will cause health problems to housewives and children , but it is still a mystery .
in 1980 - 1992 , danish researchers followed a total of 43,000 births in the country , with at least two children , and the first time of pregnancy .
when analyzing the situation , they only used the information on their previous production .
on the whole , nearly 20 per cent of the women who have been pregnant for the first time have the same experience in the second time of pregnancy .
however , when the first and second children came from different parents , the percentage fell slightly to over 15 percent .
" this has been a lot , " said the host of the research report .
this indicated that if you ( the second child ) are the same as the partners of the team , you will be much more likely to have a long time of pregnancy than 30 percent . "
" if women change the time of pregnancy in each and every time , they can reduce the danger of time - sharing , " the report said .
we believe this is a new discovery .
this means that the date of birth may be determined by the father 's gene . "
