us defense department to abolish two missile interception tests
xinhua news agency , washington , january 8 ( reporter tan xinmu ) - the us defense department 's missile defense office spokesman jose maria aznar announced on the 8 th that the us military has decided to cancel two missile interception tests scheduled for the first half of this year , because the reason for the development of a new - type booster to launch a missile intercepting missile .
aznar told the media here that the missile defense agency needs to focus on solving the problem of the booster , and the next test will be carried out by the boeing company in autumn this year after the missile intercepting rocket is produced .
the boeing company originally planned to launch a test on the new - type booster of " interception " missile in 2000 , but it was postponed due to technical reasons .
after the failure of the rocket launching in december 2001 , the boeing company decided to redesign the rocket and is scheduled to complete this autumn .
in the eight land - based interception tests that have been carried out , the us military used the modified " militia " rocket as a substitute for the booster , but the test results of this kind of booster are not ideal .
the missile interception test conducted in july 2000 and december last year failed because the " interception device " was not separated from the booster .
us president bush ordered the department of defense to start deploying the missile defense system on 17 december last year and strive to build a preliminary missile defense system by september 2004 .
however , many experts believe that as far as the technology is concerned , the time for the deployment of the missile defense system is not yet ripe .
kadish , director of the missile defense agency , also said that if the boeing company cannot produce a qualified help rocket as scheduled , the entire missile defense system will be affected .
