shanghai port transmits kaohsiung to become world 's fourth largest container port
xinhua news agency , shanghai , january 10 ( reporter feng yizhen ) - the information from the port industry , the total container throughput of shanghai port , which was completed last year , was 81.12 million teus , while the container throughput of taiwan 's kaohsiung port was about 84.91 million teus , and shanghai port surpassed kaohsiung port and became the fourth largest container port in the world .
last year , the global economic recovery and china 's sustained economic development have injected new vitality into the development of shanghai 's port .
in 2001 , the total volume of container throughput in shanghai port reached 634 million tons , and the total volume of container throughput reached 81.62 million boxes , a sharp increase of 35.8 percent over the previous year , and the total volume of cargo throughput reached 2.6 billion tons , increasing by 19 percent over the previous year , and the export volume for the first time broke through 100 million tons , an increase of 22 percent over the previous year .
shanghai port , with its vast economic hinterland , has a huge network of direct flights , and has become the largest port in the air route and the largest number of flights .
at present , shanghai port has flights in 12 of the world , and has trade contacts with more than 4,000,000 ports in the world , and is going to europe and north america every day , and there are flights to the mediterranean , the persian gulf , and australia every week .
each month , there are over 1,300 flights around the world .
the shanghai port , which is speeding up the construction of the international shipping center , will break through 9.5 million boxes this year and strive to reach 10 million teus and achieve the original target one year ahead of schedule .
