eu decides a huge diamonds deal violating discipline
xinhua news agency , brussels , january 16 ( reporter tian fan ) the european commission announced on the 16 th that the european union ( eu ) had initially identified the four - billion - euro diamond trading contract signed by the german company and the russian diamonds company , which violated the eu 's anti - monopoly law .
in south africa and britain , the company controlled 60 percent to 65 percent of the world 's unprocessed diamonds , while the russian diamond company is the only diamonds company in russia , and is also the world 's second largest unprocessed diamonds .
according to the five - year large - scale contracts signed by the two companies , the russian diamonds company agreed to provide the german company with half of the annual diamond output , which is worth about 800 million euros , and the company will be responsible for pushing the diamonds to the market .
the eu commission pointed out in a statement that the contract will restrict the free competition between russia and the world 's diamonds market and make the german company possible to abuse its leading position to effectively control the quantity , quality , and even prices of diamonds in the world .
according to the eu 's anti - monopoly law , these two companies can raise objections to the eu commission 's decision within two months , and the eu commission will continue to conduct an anti - monopoly investigation of these two companies .
