brazilian risk index down
xinhua news agency , brasilia , february 27 , ( reporter yang limin ) the brazilian national risk index dropped to 1,191 points on the 27 th , a decrease of 2.37 percent over the previous day .
this was the first time in eight months since the financial turmoil broke out in brazil in june last year , the index dropped to below 1,200 points .
at the same time , the bond issue in the international market rose 0.42 percent to 74% .
this is also the best record in eight months .
the national risk index is closely related to the bond price , the higher the index , and the lower the bond price .
last year , the brazilian national risk index exceeded 2,400 points , and the bond price dropped to 48% in value .
since the new government took office this year , the country 's risk index has continued to drop .
foreign investors believe that brazil 's bond price is low , and the demand for the bonds has increased by a big margin , which has led to a sharp decline in the risk index of brazil .
however , analysts pointed out that despite the current favorable situation of international investors in brazil 's bonds , if the us - iraq war breaks out , the national risk index may rise again and the bond prices will fall again .
